          {
            "static_group": 1,
            "group_text": [
              {
                "lang_tag": "ui7_kitdevice_7131_step_2_01",
                "text": "Turn the power back on at the electrical panel. \n<br><br>\nIf you have previously set up the Temperature format (MENU 2) and Heating Mode (MENU 3), the temperature will be displayed when you turn the power back on.\n<br><br>\nIf this is the first time powering up the thermostat, it will ask you to set the temperature format and the heating mode. \n<br><br>\nThe screen will turn on within a few seconds and you will see a flashing 'C' to indicate you are in the temperature format menu (MENU 2). Use the LEFT/RIGHT arrows to select either 'C' or 'F' then press the MIDDLE Button to confirm your selection. \n<br><br>\nNext you will see a flashing 'OFF' to indicate you are in heating mode menu (MENU 3). Press the LEFT/RIGHT arrows to select the baseboard convector 'OFF' mode or fan convector 'ON' mode. Press the MIDDLE button to confirm your selection.\n<br><br>\nNow the temperature will be displayed on the screen.\n<br><br>\nPress the 'Next' button below to continue."
              }
            ]
          }
